  "id": "low_volatility_volume_drop_strategy",
  "name": "Low Volatility Volume Drop Strategy",
  "description": "This strategy identifies periods of low daily range volatility, defined by the difference between high and low prices, that occur alongside a sequential decline in trading volume over four consecutive days. A trade is initiated based on the next day's opening gap, entering long or short positions depending on whether the open is higher or lower than the previous close.",
  "algorithm_type": "TechnicalPattern",
  "prompt": "Develop a technical pattern strategy that detects periods of unusually low daily range volatility (measured as the difference between high and low prices) that coincide with a sequential drop in trading volume over 4 consecutive days. Enter a trade in the direction of the next day's opening gap (if the open is higher than the prior close, go long; if lower, go short), but only if the current day's range is less than 50% of the 20-period average true range and each of the last 4 days' volumes is lower than its preceding day. Set take profit when price moves in favor by 1.5 times the 20-period average true range from entry and stop loss if price moves 1x ATR against the entry.",
